of the finished product.

01:10:49.270 --> 01:10:51.550 align:middle line:84%
Because our agricultural
corporations

01:10:51.550 --> 01:10:53.920 align:middle line:84%
are subsidized to
such a large degree,

01:10:53.920 --> 01:10:56.020 align:middle line:84%
they're actually
able to grow food

01:10:56.020 --> 01:10:58.840 align:middle line:84%
at lower than
world-market prices.

01:10:58.840 --> 01:11:02.860 align:middle line:84%
What this means is, we
overproduce food in the US

01:11:02.860 --> 01:11:04.450 align:middle line:90%
by about 30%.

01:11:04.450 --> 01:11:07.420 align:middle line:84%
That 30% extra
food actually gets

01:11:07.420 --> 01:11:09.850 align:middle line:84%
dumped onto the world
market at prices

01:11:09.850 --> 01:11:13.700 align:middle line:84%
